 {"id":"coding_agent_usage_tracker-1mj","title":"Errors: Fix suggestion database","description":"## Overview
Create a database of fix suggestions mapped to error types, including commands, context, and prevention tips.

## Background & Rationale
This is the knowledge base that powers actionable errors. Each error type needs curated fix suggestions that are specific, accurate, and helpful.

## Technical Approach

### 1. Fix Suggestion Structure
```rust
// In error/suggestions.rs
#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub struct FixSuggestion {
    /// Primary fix commands (in order of preference).
    pub commands: Vec<String>,

    /// Explanation of why this error occurred.
    pub context: String,

    /// Tips to prevent this error in future.
    pub prevention: Option<String>,

    /// Link to documentation.
    pub doc_url: Option<String>,

    /// Whether this can be auto-fixed.
    pub auto_fixable: bool,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub struct ErrorWithFix {
    pub error: CautError,
    pub suggestions: Vec<FixSuggestion>,
}
```

### 2. Suggestion Database
```rust
impl CautError {
    pub fn fix_suggestions(&self) -> Vec<FixSuggestion> {
        match self {
            Self::AuthExpired { provider, .. } => vec![
                FixSuggestion {
                    commands: vec![
                        format!("caut auth refresh {}", provider),
                        format!("caut auth login {}", provider),
                    ],
                    context: format!(
                        "Your OAuth token for {} has expired. Tokens are typically \
                        valid for 24 hours. The token may have been revoked if you \
                        logged out elsewhere.",
                        provider
                    ),
                    prevention: Some(
                        "Use `caut usage --watch` to monitor session health and \
                        get alerts before tokens expire.".to_string()
                    ),
                    doc_url: Some("https://github.com/.../docs/auth.md".to_string()),
                    auto_fixable: false,
                },
            ],

            Self::AuthNotConfigured { provider } => vec![
                FixSuggestion {
                    commands: vec![
                        format!("caut auth login {}", provider),
                        format!("caut setup {}", provider),
                    ],
                    context: format!(
                        "No credentials found for {}. This provider requires \
                        authentication to access usage data.",
                        provider
                    ),
                    prevention: None,
                    doc_url: Some("https://github.com/.../docs/setup.md".to_string()),
                    auto_fixable: false,
                },
            ],

            Self::Timeout { provider, seconds } => vec![
                FixSuggestion {
                    commands: vec![
                        format!("caut usage --provider {} --timeout {}", provider, seconds * 2),
                        "caut doctor --provider <provider>".to_string(),
                    ],
                    context: format!(
                        "The {} provider did not respond within {}s. This could be \
                        due to network issues, provider slowness, or the CLI tool \
                        being unresponsive.",
                        provider, seconds
                    ),
                    prevention: Some(
                        "Increase timeout with --timeout or in config file. Consider \
                        disabling slow providers if this persists.".to_string()
                    ),
                    doc_url: None,
                    auto_fixable: false,
                },
            ],

            Self::ConfigParse { path, line, message } => vec![
                FixSuggestion {
                    commands: vec![
                        format!("$EDITOR {}", path),
                        "caut config init --force".to_string(),
                    ],
                    context: format!(
                        "The config file has a syntax error{}. The TOML parser \
                        reported: {}",
                        line.map(|l| format!(" on line {}", l)).unwrap_or_default(),
                        message
                    ),
                    prevention: Some(
                        "Use `caut config show` after editing to validate config. \
                        Consider using a TOML-aware editor.".to_string()
                    ),
                    doc_url: None,
                    auto_fixable: false,
                },
            ],

            Self::CliNotFound { name } => vec![
                FixSuggestion {
                    commands: Self::install_commands_for_cli(name),
                    context: format!(
                        "The {} CLI tool is not installed or not in PATH. This \
                        provider requires the CLI to fetch usage data.",
                        name
                    ),
                    prevention: None,
                    doc_url: Self::install_doc_for_cli(name),
                    auto_fixable: false,
                },
            ],

            Self::RateLimited { provider, retry_after, .. } => vec![
                FixSuggestion {
                    commands: retry_after.map(|d| vec![
                        format!("sleep {} && caut usage --provider {}", d.as_secs(), provider)
                    ]).unwrap_or_default(),
                    context: format!(
                        "You have been rate limited by {}. {}",
                        provider,
                        retry_after.map(|d| format!("Try again in {} seconds.", d.as_secs()))
                            .unwrap_or_else(|| "Wait before retrying.".to_string())
                    ),
                    prevention: Some(
                        "Use `caut usage --watch` with longer intervals to avoid \
                        hitting rate limits.".to_string()
                    ),
                    doc_url: None,
                    auto_fixable: false,
                },
            ],

            // Default for errors without specific suggestions
            _ => vec![],
        }
    }

    fn install_commands_for_cli(name: &str) -> Vec<String> {
        match name {
            "claude" => vec![
                "npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code".to_string(),
            ],
            "codex" => vec![
                "npm install -g @openai/codex".to_string(),
            ],
            _ => vec![],
        }
    }

    fn install_doc_for_cli(name: &str) -> Option<String> {
        match name {
            "claude" => Some("https://claude.ai/code".to_string()),
            "codex" => Some("https://openai.com/codex".to_string()),
            _ => None,
        }
    }
}
