 {"id":"coding_agent_usage_tracker-1n2","title":"Config: Core loading, parsing, and validation","description":"## Overview
Implement the core configuration loading and parsing infrastructure for the caut config file.

## Background & Rationale
This is the foundation for the config system. We need reliable loading with good error messages, validation to catch mistakes early, and a clean API for the rest of the codebase to consume settings.

## Technical Approach

### 1. Config File Location
```rust
// In storage/config.rs or core/config.rs
use directories::ProjectDirs;

pub fn config_path() -> Option<PathBuf> {
    // Primary: XDG config directory
    if let Some(proj_dirs) = ProjectDirs::from("", "", "caut") {
        let config = proj_dirs.config_dir().join("config.toml");
        if config.exists() {
            return Some(config);
        }
    }

    // Fallback: home directory
    if let Some(home) = dirs::home_dir() {
        let rc = home.join(".cautrc");
        if rc.exists() {
            return Some(rc);
        }
    }

    None
}
```

### 2. Config Structure
```rust
#[derive(Debug, Deserialize, Default)]
#[serde(default)]
pub struct Config {
    pub defaults: DefaultsConfig,
    pub providers: HashMap<String, ProviderConfig>,
    pub output: OutputConfig,
}

#[derive(Debug, Deserialize, Default)]
#[serde(default)]
pub struct DefaultsConfig {
    pub providers: Option<Vec<String>>,
    pub format: Option<String>,  // "human", "json", "md"
    pub timeout_seconds: Option<u64>,
    pub no_color: bool,
    pub verbose: bool,
}

#[derive(Debug, Deserialize, Default)]
#[serde(default)]
pub struct ProviderConfig {
    pub enabled: bool,
    pub priority: Option<i32>,
    pub timeout_seconds: Option<u64>,
    // Provider-specific settings can be added
}

#[derive(Debug, Deserialize, Default)]
#[serde(default)]
pub struct OutputConfig {
    pub pretty: bool,
    pub quiet: bool,
}
```

### 3. Loading with Error Handling
```rust
impl Config {
    pub fn load() -> Result<Self> {
        match config_path() {
            Some(path) => Self::load_from(&path),
            None => Ok(Self::default()),
        }
    }

    pub fn load_from(path: &Path) -> Result<Self> {
        let content = fs::read_to_string(path)
            .map_err(|e| CautError::Config(format\!(
                "Failed to read config at {}: {}", path.display(), e
            )))?;

        toml::from_str(&content)
            .map_err(|e| CautError::Config(format\!(
                "Invalid config at {}: {}", path.display(), e
            )))
    }
}
```

### 4. Validation
```rust
impl Config {
    pub fn validate(&self) -> Result<()> {
        // Validate provider names
        if let Some(providers) = &self.defaults.providers {
            for name in providers {
                Provider::from_cli_name(name)?;
            }
        }

        // Validate format
        if let Some(format) = &self.defaults.format {
            if \!["human", "json", "md"].contains(&format.as_str()) {
                return Err(CautError::Config(format\!(
                    "Invalid format \"{}\". Valid: human, json, md", format
                )));
            }
        }

        // Validate timeouts (reasonable bounds)
        if let Some(timeout) = self.defaults.timeout_seconds {
            if timeout == 0 || timeout > 300 {
                return Err(CautError::Config(
                    "Timeout must be between 1 and 300 seconds".to_string()
                ));
            }
        }

        Ok(())
    }
}
```

